commit.message: Updating firmware.bin
Changed hot end PID values to be more realistic for an E3D v6 or Kraken. Also, added PID settings for heated bed. They're useful if you have an Onyx.
Whitespace, and credit PyjamaSam for helping debug.

Disabled the new 'P' G-code option that lets you send the command to an alternate strategy, because it breaks the 'P' code used by both G29 and G31, and also because in this context, it's largely useless. People are not downloading my fork, so that they can use a strategy I didn't write. I also fixed G30 - thanks PyjamaSam!

Partially backed out changes to ZProbe::wait_for_probe(). We no longer average the three steppers' steps traveled, but we still collect Z's steps immediately rather than doing it after the axes have been commanded to stop. Repeatability is much improved.
